('proj-web-appsec-lab-report', 'ph-web-appsec', 4, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required Web AppSec Lab Report', 'Milestone project: Complete authorized web security labs and write a professional findings/remediation report.', 'side', 8, 'intermediate', '{"whatToBuild":"Complete authorized web security labs and write a professional findings/remediation report.","buildSteps":["Define the Web AppSec Lab Report scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: security controls.","Define the asset, threat scenario, assumptions, and rules of engagement for the lab or assessment.","Collect evidence through configuration review, controlled testing, logs, diagrams, or sample findings.","Map each finding to an impact, likelihood, mitigation, and verification step.","Write a concise report that separates observed evidence from assumptions and recommendations.","Keep the scope focused enough to complete, review, and explain the a Web AppSec Lab Report security assessment, lab, or hardening artifact with findings and mitigations.","Document how to run or review the Web AppSec Lab Report deliverable, including inputs, expected outputs, and known limitations."],"source":"roadmap.sh/cyber-security","nodeKey":"proj-web-appsec-lab-report"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Apply Web, API, and Application Security through a focused Web AppSec Lab Report artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a Web AppSec Lab Report security assessment, lab, or hardening artifact with findings and mitigations is available for review.","The Web AppSec Lab Report scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
